<div class="markdown-heading" dir="auto"><h2 tabindex="-1" class="heading-element" dir="auto">Notice</h2><a id="user-content-notice" class="anchor" aria-label="Permalink: Notice" href="#notice"><svg data-component="Octicon" class="octicon octicon-link" viewBox="0 0 16 16" version="1.1" width="16" height="16" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m7.775 3.275 1.25-1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1 4.95 4.95l-2.5 2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1-4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1 .018-1.042.751.751 0 0 1 1.042-.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l2.5-2.5a2.002 2.002 0 0 0-2.83-2.83l-1.25 1.25a.751.751 0 0 1-1.042-.018.751.751 0 0 1-.018-1.042Zm-4.69 9.64a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 2.83 0l1.25-1.25a.751.751 0 0 1 1.042.018.751.751 0 0 1 .018 1.042l-1.25 1.25a3.5 3.5 0 1 1-4.95-4.95l2.5-2.5a3.5 3.5 0 0 1 4.95 0 .751.751 0 0 1-.018 1.042.751.751 0 0 1-1.042.018 1.998 1.998 0 0 0-2.83 0l-2.5 2.5a1.998 1.998 0 0 0 0 2.83Z"></path></svg></a></div>
<p dir="auto">This module is published for consumption from our own drivers, such as the <a href="https://github.com/neo4j/neo4j-java-driver">Neo4j Java Driver</a> and the <a href="https://github.com/neo4j/neo4j-jdbc">Neo4j JDBC Driver</a>.
No support is offered for this module and no API guarantees are given, and we will evolve this module as we see fit.
This module should not be used by end-users, please use one of the drivers mentioned above for Java applications.</p>
<p dir="auto">No pull-requests will be accepted.</p>
